1 both volunteer and career Emergency Medical Services personnel who have lost their lives in
2 service to the state; and
3 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Capitol Grounds Planning Commission collaborate
4 with the Emergency Medical Services Division of the Department of Health and Human
5 Services, the North Dakota Emergency Medical Services Association, and other associated
6 organizations to ensure the memorial appropriately reflects the sacrifices of these individuals;
7 and
8 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Capitol Grounds Planning Commission explore
9 potential funding sources, including public and private donations, grants, and other appropriate
10 sources, to finance the design, construction, and maintenance of the memorial; and
11 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Secretary of State forward copies of this resolution
12 to the members of the Capitol Grounds Planning Commission and the Director of the North
13 Dakota Office of Management and Budget.
